	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-10-02T10:01:58">London Finance &amp; Investment Group P.L.C. is a United Kingdom investment finance and management company. The Company's objective is to generate growth in shareholder value in real terms over the medium to long term, while maintaining a progressive dividend policy. The Company's investment policy is to invest in a range of strategic investments, a general portfolio consisting of liquid stock market investments, both in equity instruments and bonds, and other investments, typically property and other physical assets. The Company's strategic investments include Western Selection P.L.C. and Finsbury Food Group Plc. Its general portfolio is with material interests in Food and Beverages, Natural Resources, Chemicals and Tobacco. The Company's subsidiary, City Group P.L.C., provides management, office and company secretarial services. City Group P.L.C. also provides office accommodation, company secretarial and head office finance services to the other United Kingdom and Jersey companies.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-11-02T01:10:03">BRIEF: For the fiscal year ended 30 June 2015, London Finance &amp; Investment Group plc revenues increased 10% to L977K. Net income totaled L2M vs. loss of L43K. Revenues reflect Dividends  Listed investments increase of 24% to L487K, Management services fees increase of 14% to L233K. Net Income reflects Unrealised changes in the carrying value increase from L339K (expense) to L2M (income), Administration expenses decrease of 1% to L643K (expense).</Text>
